{
  "tool": "get_all_car_rental_companies_in_city",
  "args": {
    "city": "Los Angeles"
  }
}
{
  "tool": "get_car_fuel_options",
  "args": {
    "company_name": "<tool_result_0/>"
  }
}
{
  "tool": "get_car_types_available",
  "args": {
    "company_name": "<tool_result_0/>"
  }
}
{
  "tool": "get_rating_reviews_for_car_rental",
  "args": {
    "company_name": "<tool_result_0/>"
  }
}
{
  "tool": "get_car_price_per_day",
  "args": {
    "company_name": "<tool_result_0/>"
  }
}
{
  "tool": "query_llm",
  "args": {
    "prompt": "Given the following data about car rental companies in Los Angeles:\n\nCar companies: <tool_result_0/>\nFuel options for each company: <tool_result_1/>\nCar types available for each company: <tool_result_2/>\nRatings for each company (numeric rating out of 5): <tool_result_3/>\nPrice per day for each company (in USD): <tool_result_4/>\n\nIdentify the car rental company that offers electric cars (fuel option includes 'Electric') with the highest rating, and the car rental company that offers SUVs (car type includes 'SUV') with the highest rating. For each, provide the company name, rating, and total cost for 3 days (price per day multiplied by 3). Output the result in the following format:\n\nElectric Car Rental: <Company Name> - Rating: <rating> - Cost for 3 days: $<cost>\nSUV Rental: <Company Name> - Rating: <rating> - Cost for 3 days: $<cost>"
  }
}
<tool_result_5/>
